Two-Wheel Robot in Onshape

In this project, we present the mechanical design of a differential-drive robot that has been designed in Onshape. It consists of a small chassis suitable for educational purposes and depicted in CAR ONSHAPE_2.jpeg. As seen in the diagram, it comprises two tiers of construction for efficient space management. The top one represents an open space covered by a light blue panel with holes for mounting various devices, such as microcontrollers and sensors. Underneath, there is a sealed-off area that contains all the heavy elements of the robot, including the battery pack and electric motors, thus reducing its center of mass and increasing stability during movement.

The locomotion mechanism is based on a simple yet efficient approach – two wheels driven by a differential drive system fitted with rubber tires and customized orange three-spoke rims to increase traction. Thus, zero radius turns become possible, allowing for excellent maneuverability at any moment. The whole design in Onshape is also characterized by its simplicity, since it features only two planes of flat surfaces of identical thickness. They could be easily produced by modern manufacturing technologies.
